20/03/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Parliament Chairman Zlatko Tomcic wrapped up a visit to Brussels on Wednesday (19 March) and said he heard significant encouragement for Croatia's accession to the EU.
He told reporters that the European Community would assess Zagreb's membership application in about a year.
Tomcic predicted the country could join Bulgaria and Romania's timetable, becoming a full EU member in 2007.
(HRT, HINA - 19/03/03)
